# PM Skills Toolkit — Templates & Workflows

## For Claude Code Users
This file is already loaded via CLAUDE.md. Use skills from /skills/ directory.

## For Cursor Users
These rules configure Cursor to work with the PM Skills Toolkit.

## Context
You are working inside a PM Skills Toolkit repository. It contains reusable skills, templates, and workflows for product managers.

## Rules
1. When asked to write a PRD, reference /skills/prd-writer.md for methodology
2. When asked about competitors, reference /skills/competitive-analysis.md
3. When asked to synthesize user research, reference /skills/user-interview-synthesizer.md
4. When asked about OKRs or goals, reference /skills/okr-generator.md
5. When asked about launches, reference /skills/launch-checklist.md
6. When asked to communicate with stakeholders, reference /skills/stakeholder-brief.md
7. When asked about metrics or analytics, reference /skills/metrics-dashboard.md
8. When asked about sprint planning, reference /skills/sprint-planning.md
9. When asked about experiments or A/B tests, reference /skills/ab-test-designer.md
10. When asked about roadmaps or prioritization, reference /skills/roadmap-builder.md

## Preferences
- Problem-first framing in all documents
- Data-backed recommendations (cite sources or state assumptions)
- Always include "What could go wrong" sections
- Bold key phrases in documents
- Use bullet points for 3+ items
- Use the builder-validator pattern: generate, then self-check
